Regular and irregular verbs of the present indicative, reflexive verbs, direct object, past perfect, the use of the verbs to know (saber) and to be able (poder).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acquire the lower intermediate level of Spanish (A2) and introduce the students to some aspects of Spanish and Latin American cultures and history.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the learners will be able to read and understand simple texts (both oral and written) and use the vocabulary and grammar covered during the course in everyday situations. The learners will be able to talk and write about her/his home and eating habits, to express (dis)approval and to socialize in the street, in the shop, at a restaurant, in a group. The learners will be able  to understand and to create the elementary oral and written texts.
